Date of Birth: July 29, 1915<br/>
Birthplace: Ann Arbor, Michigan, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: October 12, 1972<br/>
Death: April 19, 1985<br/>
<br/>
Born July 29, 1915, at Ann Arbor, Washtenaw Co., Michigan, to Oscar Walter McConkie and Vivian Redd. Sustained to First Council of the Seventy Oct. 6, 1946, at age 31; ordained apostle Oct. 12, 1972, by Harold B. Lee, at age 57; died April 19, 1985, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 69.